":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikemee","html_url":"https://github.com/mikemee","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikemee/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikemee/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikemee/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikemee/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikemee/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikemee/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikemee/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikemee/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikemee/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2017-10-02T23:05:08Z","updated_at":"2017-10-02T23:05:08Z","body":"> VerticalGroup always aligns its elements to center independently of the alignment setting. \r\n\r\nIn case someone else notices this and is looking for the quick fix.  For my code, _YMMV!_, I was able to replace:\r\n```java\r\n\tprivate final VerticalGroup stack = new VerticalGroup();\r\n        ....\r\n        // add rows of horizontalGroups to the stack\r\n        ....\r\n        stack.align(align);\r\n```\r\nwith\r\n```\r\n\tprivate final VerticalGroup stack = new VerticalGroup();\r\n        ....\r\n        stack.columnAlign(align);\r\n```\r\nAnd then all was right with the world again.","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/333690062/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"mikemee","id":550990,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1MDk5MA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/550990?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikemee","html_url":"https://github.com/mikemee","followers_url":"https